<br>
When t-rods were nerfed and mages everywhere cried out.  VI said..Hey, we're doing what you wanted us to do, we're re-rolling you as a top-notch damage dealers.<br>
<br>
We responded by saying...Ok, but don't f*&amp;% around.  If you're gonna say that, we better see some noticeable increases.  We have...and there's nothing wrong with that.  <br>
<br>
Using tricks like pet cani is only using all your skills and game mechanics to be at your best.  Rogues do the same thing when they circle strafe and evade.  If the issue has been brought forth to VI as a possible bug and they respond that it's like that on purpose and then put AA's in place to make it even better....I don't see the problem?<br>
<br>
People are going to bitch, not because we are overpowered, but because we are balanced competition for the coveted damage dealing spot in groups.  The issues are no longer about balance as much, but more about stacking.  We are one more legitimate damage dealer amongst many, and THAT is why people are going to bitch.  Not because we are overpowered, but because they can't laugh at us anymore.  That 65 monk (most likely an ex-mage's twink <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) that goes LFG at the same time as the 65 mage can't laugh to him/herself anymore at how sad his &quot;competition&quot; is, and stands just as good a chance at staying LFG as the mage does now.<br>
<br>
And if I hear complaints from druids about this, all I can do is laugh.  I'm damage..that's all I am.  I cannot main heal a group in a pinch....EVER.  Druids trade supremecy over one task to be good at many (and I mean MANY).  Mages should provide far superior DPS to druids, that is a no-brainer.  <p><p align=center>
